

Prep 
1.  If you configured Splunk Enterprise to start on boot, remove it from your boot scripts before you uninstall.

	sudo su 

	/opt/splunk/bin/splunk disable boot-start


2. Stop Splunk Enterprise

	/opt/splunk/bin/splunk stop

3. Find and kill any lingering processes that contain "splunk" in their name.

	kill -9 `ps -ef | grep splunk | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2;}'`

4. Remove the Splunk Enterprise installation directory-$SPLUNK_HOME.

	rm -rf /opt/splunk


5. Remove any Splunk Enterprise datastore or indexes outside the top-level directory, if they exist.
	
	rm -rf /opt/splunkdata


6. Delete the splunk user and group, if they exist.

	groupdel splunk
	userdel splunk


sudo su 
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk disable boot-start
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk stop
rm -rf /opt/splunk




Note: 

cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd


/opt/splunk/bin/splunk disable boot-start
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk stop



Removing Splunk - simple way

1. login into server with splunk installed
2. changed user to splunk : sudo su - splunk
3. stopped splunk: cd /opt/splunk/bin
./splunk stop
4. check splunk process wasnt running 
./splunk status
5. login as root : exit 
sudo su 
6. change directory to $SPLUNK_HOME - cd /opt/
always ls to see whats in the directory before deleting
7. remove splunk directory
rm -Rf splunk 


